topIssues.title: oncall: check-for-changes step is failing intermittently in CI
topIssues.author: janjakubnanista
topIssues.body:
**Description**

There is an issue with the `checkout` workaround/speedup:

- In the `initialize` job, we checkout the code. The checkout step is important since it includes adding known hosts for all VCS
- We persist the code to the workspace
- In the "optimized" jobs we only take the persisted code but not the SSH configuration

[Slack thread here](https://oplabs-pbc.slack.com/archives/CQZ0U9FAN/p1762954516296549)

[Failing workflow](https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ethereum-optimism/optimism/107390/workflows/d1ec591e-ed64-4b81-811d-885df61f665c/jobs/4089882)

[PR that passed the check](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/18254)
[PR that failed the check](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/17751)
